'''Cheikh Bouamama''' or '''Shaykh Bu 'Amamah''' ({{lang-ar|الشيخ بوعمامة}}) led an insurrection in [[Algeria]] from 1881 to 1883.{{sfn|Aghrout|2005|p=86}}

Cheikh Bouamama was a leader of the [[Awlad Sidi Shaykh]] confederation.{{sfn|Sivers|2012}}
The rebellion that he led in the southwest of Algeria from 1881 to 1883 fell apart due to disagreements among the tribes.{{sfn|Krause|2017|loc=PT175}}
When Cheikh Bouamama retreated to Morocco in 1882 the French conquest of the south of Algeria was complete.{{sfn|Sivers|2012}}

The Algerian filmmaker Benamar Bakhti made the 1983 film ''L'Épopée de Cheikh Bouamama'' ("The Epic of Cheikh Bouamama").{{sfn|Armes|2005|p=191}}

