'''Hussein Quwaian Al-Mutairi''' is a member of the [[National Assembly of Kuwait|Kuwaiti National Assembly]], representing the fourth district. Born in 1968, Hussein Al-Mutairi worked as a doctor before being elected to the National Assembly in 2008. While political parties are technically illegal in Kuwait, Al-Mutairi affiliates with the Islamist and tribal deputies. He is a member of the [[Al-Mutairi]] tribe.<ref>[https://www.arabtimesonline.com/pdf08/may/19/page%2009.pdf Arab Times MP Profile]{{dead link|date=April 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>
