| alt2 = Freddie Mercury performing
| align = right}}

During the early stages of her career, Perry's musical style gravitated towards gospel and she aspired to be as successful as [[Amy Grant]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Katy Perry on the 180 That Saved Her Career|url=https://www.npr.org/2013/10/26/240760441/katy-perry-returns-with-a-roar|publisher=[[NPR]]|date=October 26, 2013|accessdate=February 3, 2014|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140218225808/http://www.npr.org/2013/10/26/240760441/katy-perry-returns-with-a-roar|archivedate=February 18, 2014}}</ref> At the age of 15, she heard [[Queen (band)|Queen]]'s "[[Killer Queen]]," which inspired her to pursue a career in music.<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Schneider|first=Marc|title=Katy Perry Wants a 'Fucking Vacation' After Next Single|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/488619/katy-perry-wants-a-f-ing-vacation-after-next-single|magazine=Billboard|accessdate=February 3, 2014|date=May 12, 2012|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140713083643/http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/488619/katy-perry-wants-a-f-ing-vacation-after-next-single|archivedate=July 13, 2014}}</ref> She cites the band's frontman, [[Freddie Mercury]], as her biggest influence and expressed how the "combination of his sarcastic approach to writing lyrics and his 'I don't give a fuck' attitude" inspired her music.<ref>{{cite magazine|title=Freddie Mercury inspired Katy Perry to 'Kiss a Girl'|url=http://www.nme.com/news/queen/40017|magazine=[[NME]]|date=September 26, 2008|accessdate=February 3, 2014|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140106041511/http://www.nme.com/news/queen/40017|archivedate=January 6, 2014}}</ref> She paid homage to the band by naming her third fragrance Killer Queen.<ref name="killerqueen1"/> Perry described [[The Beach Boys]] and their album ''[[Pet Sounds]]'' as having a considerable influence on her music: "''Pet Sounds'' is one of my favorite records and it influenced pretty much all of my songwriting. All of the melody choices that I make are because of ''Pet Sounds''."<ref>{{cite web|title=Katy Perry, The Things They Say|url=http://www.contactmusic.com/story/the-things-they-say_3902539|publisher=Contactmusic.com|accessdate=February 3, 2014|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222131051/http://www.contactmusic.com/story/the-things-they-say_3902539|archivedate=February 22, 2014}}</ref> The singer also holds [[the Beatles]]' album ''[[The Beatles (album)|The Beatles]]'' in high esteem, and described these two albums as "the only things I listened to for probably two years straight."<ref name=InterviewWiig>{{cite magazine|last=Wiig|first=Kristen|authorlink=Kristen Wiig|title=Katy Perry|url=http://www.interviewmagazine.com/music/katy-perry#page4|magazine=[[Interview (magazine)|Interview]]|accessdate=February 3, 2014|date=March 2, 2012|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222061428/http://www.interviewmagazine.com/music/katy-perry|archivedate=February 22, 2014}}</ref>

Perry cites [[Alanis Morissette]] and her 1995 album ''[[Jagged Little Pill]]'' as a significant musical inspiration, and opted to work with Morissette's frequent collaborator Ballard as a result. Perry stated, "''Jagged Little Pill'' was the most perfect female record ever made. There's a song for anyone on that record; I relate to all those songs. They're still so timeless." Additionally, Perry borrows influence from ''[[Flaming Red]]'' by [[Patty Griffin]] and ''10 Cent Wings'' by [[Jonatha Brooke]].<ref name=BillboardQA>{{cite magazine|last=Mitchell|first=Gail|title=Katy Perry Q&A: Billboard's Woman of the Year 2012|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/473939/katy-perry-qa-billboards-woman-of-the-year-2012?page=0%2C1|magazine=Billboard|date=November 30, 2012|accessdate=November 30, 2012|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130508091858/http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/473939/katy-perry-qa-billboards-woman-of-the-year-2012?page=0%2C1|archivedate=May 8, 2013}}</ref> Perry intends to become "more of a [[Joni Mitchell]]", releasing folk and acoustic music.<ref name="peniston">{{cite news|last=Michaels|first=Sean|title=Katy Perry wants to go folk acoustic&nbsp;– in style of Joni Mitchell|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2013/oct/01/katy-perry-plans-acoustic-folk-album|newspaper=The Guardian|accessdate=February 3, 2014|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140223005644/http://www.theguardian.com/music/2013/oct/01/katy-perry-plans-acoustic-folk-album|archivedate=February 23, 2014}}</ref> Perry's autobiographical documentary ''Katy Perry: Part of Me'' was largely influenced by ''[[Madonna: Truth or Dare]]''. She admires Madonna's ability to reinvent herself, saying "I want to evolve like Madonna",<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1682661/katy-perry-part-of-me-movie.jhtml|title=Katy Perry's 'Part of Me' Film Inspired By Madonna|first=James|last=Dinh|publisher=MTV News|date=April 6, 2012|accessdate=April 29, 2014|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131109132227/http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1682661/katy-perry-part-of-me-movie.jhtml|archivedate=November 9, 2013}}</ref> and has credited Madonna for inspiring her to make ''Prism'' "darker" than her previous material.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1688744/katy-perry-album-madonna-inspired/|title=Katy Perry Inspired By Madonna For 'Darker' Next Album|first=Jocelyn|last=Vena|publisher=MTV News|date=June 29, 2012|accessdate=March 25, 2016|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160410012759/http://www.mtv.com/news/1688744/katy-perry-album-madonna-inspired/|archivedate=April 10, 2016}}</ref>

Perry names [[Björk]] as an influence, particularly admiring her "willingness to always be taking chances".<ref name=BillboardQA /> Other musicians who Perry has cited as influences include [[ABBA]], [[The Cardigans]],<ref>{{cite web|first=Melinda|last=Newman|url=http://www.hitfix.com/blogs/the-beat-goes-on/posts/katy-perry-gives-hitfix-the-scoop-on-her-new-album|title=Katy Perry dishes details on new dance-fueled album|publisher=[[HitFix]]|date=April 22, 2010|accessdate=March 30, 2016|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160409020302/http://www.hitfix.com/blogs/the-beat-goes-on/posts/katy-perry-gives-hitfix-the-scoop-on-her-new-album|archivedate=April 9, 2016}}</ref> [[Cyndi Lauper]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/2295376/what-will-katy-perrys-new-album-sound-like-check-out-5-video-clues/|title=What Will Katy Perry’s New Album Sound Like? Check Out 5 Video Clues|first=Chris|last=Ryan|publisher=MTV News|date=March 30, 2010|accessdate=March 26, 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160410034805/http://www.mtv.com/news/2295376/what-will-katy-perrys-new-album-sound-like-check-out-5-video-clues/|archivedate=April 10, 2016}}</ref> [[Ace of Base]], [[3OH!3]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1622080/katy-perry-wants-to-make-new-music-her-fans-can-roller-skate-to/|title=Katy Perry wants to make new music her fans can 'roller-stake' to|first=Jocelyn|last=Vena|publisher=MTV News|date=September 22, 2009|accessdate=March 25, 2016|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160306125009/http://www.mtv.com/news/1622080/katy-perry-wants-to-make-new-music-her-fans-can-roller-skate-to/|archivedate=March 6, 2016}}</ref> [[CeCe Peniston]], [[C+C Music Factory]], [[Black Box (band)|Black Box]], [[Crystal Waters]], [[Mariah Carey]],<ref name="peniston"/> [[Heart (band)|Heart]], Joni Mitchell, [[Paul Simon]], [[Imogen Heap]], [[Rufus Wainwright]],<ref>{{cite web|last1=Garland|first1=Emma|title=A Deep Dive into Katy Perry’s 2007 Myspace Page|url=https://noisey.vice.com/en_us/article/a-deep-dive-into-katy-perrys-2007-myspace-page|website=Noisey|publisher=Vice Media|date=January 10, 2017|accessdate=January 20, 2017|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170202085355/https://noisey.vice.com/en_us/article/a-deep-dive-into-katy-perrys-2007-myspace-page|archivedate=February 2, 2017}}</ref> [[Pink (singer)|Pink]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/news/a171556/katy-perry-praises-really-great-pink.html|title=Katy Perry praises 'really great' Pink&nbsp;– Music News|publisher=''Digital Spy''|date=August 15, 2009|accessdate=December 5, 2013|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131104231134/http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/news/a171556/katy-perry-praises-really-great-pink.html|archivedate=November 4, 2013}}</ref> and [[Gwen Stefani]].<ref name=BillboardQA /> "Firework" was inspired by a passage in the book ''[[On the Road]]'' by [[Jack Kerouac]] in which the author compares people who are full of life to fireworks that shoot across the sky and make people watch in awe.<ref>{{harvnb|Friedlander|2012|p=123}}</ref> Her second concert tour, the California Dreams Tour, was reminiscent of ''[[Alice's Adventures in Wonderland]]'' and ''[[The Wonderful Wizard of Oz]]''.<ref>{{cite magazine|title=Katy Perry's 'California Dreams' Tour: What the Critics Are Saying|magazine=The Hollywood Reporter|date=June 19, 2011|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/katy-perrys-california-dreams-tour-203209|accessdate=August 6, 2014|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140908070039/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/katy-perrys-california-dreams-tour-203209|archivedate=September 8, 2014}}</ref> She also credits the 1996 movie ''[[The Craft (film)|The Craft]]'' for inspiring her song "Dark Horse",<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Rutherford|first=Kevin|title=Katy Perry Reveals 'Prism' Influences, Adds Stripped-Down Performances at Album Release Event|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/5763220/katy-perry-reveals-prism-influences-adds-stripped-down|magazine=Billboard|date=October 22, 2013|accessdate=December 9, 2013|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131027052306/http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/5763220/katy-perry-reveals-prism-influences-adds-stripped-down|archivedate=October 27, 2013}}</ref> and [[Eckhart Tolle]]'s book ''[[The Power of Now]]'' for influencing ''Prism''.<ref name=BillboardCoverStory/>

===Musical style and themes===
{{Quote box|width=30em|align=right|quote="When I am in between records, sometimes I doubt myself. I'll be like 'Did I just get lucky, or did I mass-manipulate the world into thinking that seven songs were worth a number-one position?' And then I go back into the studio and I start writing, and the true essential oil of who I am comes bubbling back up and reminds me that it's always been inside of me, that nobody can take this away no matter what comment anyone makes."|source=—Perry on her confidence as a songwriter<ref name="Vogue">{{cite magazine|last=Woods|first=Vicki|title=Katy Perry's First Vogue Cover|url=http://www.vogue.com/magazine/article/beauty-and-the-beat-katy-perrys-first-vogue-cover/#1|magazine=[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]]|date=June 2013|accessdate=July 26, 2013|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130726121649/http://www.vogue.com/magazine/article/beauty-and-the-beat-katy-perrys-first-vogue-cover/|archivedate=July 26, 2013|df=}}</ref>}}

While Perry's music incorporates [[pop music|pop]], [[rock music|rock]], and [[disco]], ''Katy Hudson'' contains gospel. Her subsequent releases, ''One of the Boys'' and ''Teenage Dream'', involve themes of sex and love. ''One of the Boys'' is a [[pop rock]] record, while ''Teenage Dream'' features disco influences.<ref>Musical genres of ''Katy Hudson'' and ''One of the Boys'':
* {{harvnb|Friedlander|2012|p=20}}
* {{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2008/sep/14/popandrock20|newspaper=The Guardian|title=Pop review: Katy Perry, One of the Boys|date=September 14, 2008|first=Stephanie|last=Merritt|accessdate=August 6, 2014|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140810174116/http://www.theguardian.com/music/2008/sep/14/popandrock20|archivedate=August 10, 2014}}
* {{cite web|last=Erlewine|first=Stephen Thomas|title=''One of the Boys''&nbsp;– Katy Perry|url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/one-of-the-boys-mw0000787236|publisher=AllMusic|accessdate=July 25, 2014|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140727192917/http://www.allmusic.com/album/one-of-the-boys-mw0000787236|archivedate=July 27, 2014}}</ref><ref name=SheffieldDream>{{cite magazine|last=Sheffield|first=Rob|authorlink=Rob Sheffield|title=Teenage Dream|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/albumreviews/teenage-dream-20100823|magazine=Rolling Stone|accessdate=February 5, 2014|date=August 23, 2010|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140125093925/http://www.rollingstone.com/music/albumreviews/teenage-dream-20100823|archivedate=January 25, 2014}}</ref> Perry's fourth album, ''Prism'', is significantly influenced by dance and pop music. Lyrically, the album addresses relationships, self-reflection, and everyday life.<ref name="PrismPicks">{{cite magazine|last=Trust|first=Gary|title=Katy Perry's Future 'Prism' Hits: Industry Picks|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/5687255/katy-perrys-future-prism-hits-industry-picks|magazine=Billboard|accessdate=September 19, 2013|date=September 9, 2013|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130911205056/http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/5687255/katy-perrys-future-prism-hits-industry-picks|archivedate=September 11, 2013}}</ref> The singer's fifth studio effort ''Witness'' is an [[electropop]] album that she described as a "360-degree liberation" record, with themes including political liberation, sexual liberation, and liberation from negativity.<ref name=WitnessLiberation>{{cite news|last1=Heller|first1=Corinne|title=Katy Perry Reveals Meaning Behind "Swish Swish" Amid Rumors Song Is About Taylor Swift|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/855182/katy-perry-reveals-meaning-behind-swish-swish-amid-rumors-song-is-about-taylor-swift|accessdate=July 25, 2017|publisher=E!|date=May 20, 2017}}</ref><ref name=WitnessGenre>{{cite magazine|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/7825915/katy-perry-witness-purposeful-pop-defense|title=Katy Perry's 'Witness' Fails as 'Purposeful Pop,' But Succeeds as Future Pop|magazine=Billboard|date=June 13, 2017|accessdate=June 16, 2017}}</ref> Many of her songs, particularly on ''Teenage Dream'', reflect on love between teenagers; ''[[W (magazine)|W]]'' described the album's sexual innuendos as "irresistible hook-laden melodies".<ref name=WMag/> Self-empowerment is a common theme in Perry's music.<ref>{{cite news|last=Reed|first=James|title=Perry shows many colors on 'Prism'|url=https://www.bostonglobe.com/arts/music/2013/10/20/perry-shows-many-colors-prism/fIMiSxHkP3V3r4yN5Z8r4H/story.html|newspaper=[[The Boston Globe]]|accessdate=February 7, 2014|date=October 20, 2013|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140125095113/http://www.bostonglobe.com/arts/music/2013/10/20/perry-shows-many-colors-prism/fIMiSxHkP3V3r4yN5Z8r4H/story.html|archivedate=January 25, 2014}}</ref>

Perry describes herself as a "[[singer-songwriter]] masquerading as a pop star"<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Wallace|first=Amy|title=Katy Perry's GQ Profile Outtakes: Going Back to School, Dating Musicians, and Plastic Surgery|url=https://www.gq.com/blogs/the-feed/2014/02/cover-katy-perry-interview-outtakes.html|magazine=GQ|date=January 19, 2014|accessdate=February 1, 2014|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140224060306/http://www.gq.com/blogs/the-feed/2014/02/cover-katy-perry-interview-outtakes.html|archivedate=February 24, 2014}}</ref> and maintains that honest songwriting is very important to her. She told ''[[Marie Claire]]'': "I feel like my secret magic trick that separates me from a lot of my peers is the bravery to be vulnerable and truthful and honest. I think you become more relatable when you're vulnerable."<ref name=Marie/> [[Kristen Wiig]] commented that "as easy, breezy, and infectious as Perry's songs can be, beneath the surface lurks a sea of mixed emotions, jumbled motives, and contradictory impulses complicated enough to fill a [[Carole King]] record."<ref name=InterviewWiig/> According to [[Greg Kot]] of the ''[[Chicago Tribune]]'', "being taken seriously may be Perry's greatest challenge yet."<ref>{{cite news|last=Kot|first=Greg|authorlink=Greg Kot|title=Katy Perry album review; Prism reviewed|url=http://articles.chicagotribune.com/2013-10-20/entertainment/chi-kate-perry-prism-review-20131020_1_katy-perry-russell-brand-album-review|newspaper=[[Chicago Tribune]]|accessdate=February 5, 2014|date=October 20, 2013|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140125230556/http://articles.chicagotribune.com/2013-10-20/entertainment/chi-kate-perry-prism-review-20131020_1_katy-perry-russell-brand-album-review|archivedate=January 25, 2014}}</ref> ''[[The New York Times]]'' labeled her "the most potent pop star of the day&nbsp;– her hits are relatable with just a hint of experimentation".<ref>{{cite news|newspaper=The New York Times|date=September 6, 2013|accessdate=August 7, 2014|title=Fall Pop Music Preview: An Abundance of Rhythms and Styles|url=http://nytimes.com/2013/09/08/arts/music/fall-pop-music-preview-an-abundance-of-rhythms-and-styles.html|first1=Jon|last1=Pareles|first2=Ben|last2=Ratliff|first3=Jon|last3=Carmanica|first4=Nate|last4=Chinen|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140811005927/http://www.nytimes.com/2013/09/08/arts/music/fall-pop-music-preview-an-abundance-of-rhythms-and-styles.html|archivedate=August 11, 2014}}</ref> Randall Roberts of the ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'' criticized her use of idioms and metaphors in her lyrics and for frequent "clichés".<ref name=LATimesReview>{{cite news|last=Roberts|first=Randall|title=Review: Hits pack Katy Perry's 'Prism'|url=http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/music/posts/la-et-ms-katy-perry-prism-review-20131022,0,6156766.story|newspaper=Los Angeles Times|accessdate=February 4, 2014|date=October 22, 2013|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140125034828/http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/music/posts/la-et-ms-katy-perry-prism-review-20131022%2C0%2C6156766.story|archivedate=January 25, 2014}}</ref> Throughout her career, Perry has co-written songs recorded by other artists, including [[Selena Gomez & the Scene]],<ref name=RockGodSelena>{{cite news|last=Vena|first=Jocelyn|title=Selena Gomez 'Had To Fight' To Get Katy Perry Song 'Rock God'|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1648390/selena-gomez-had-fight-get-katy-perry-song-rock-god.jhtml|publisher=MTV News|accessdate=September 22, 2010|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140203015006/http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1648390/selena-gomez-had-fight-get-katy-perry-song-rock-god.jhtml|archivedate=February 3, 2014}}</ref><ref name=MoreLikeIt>{{cite AV media notes|title=[[When the Sun Goes Down (Selena Gomez & the Scene album)|When the Sun Goes Down]]|others=[[Selena Gomez & the Scene]]|year=2011|publisher=[[Hollywood Records]]}}</ref> [[Jessie James]],<ref>{{cite AV media notes|title=Jessie James|others=[[Jessie James Decker|Jessie James]]|year=2009|publisher=[[Mercury Records]]/[[The Island Def Jam Music Group]]}}</ref> [[Kelly Clarkson]],<ref name=AllKellyWanted>{{cite AV media notes|title=[[All I Ever Wanted (album)|All I Ever Wanted]]|others=[[Kelly Clarkson]]|year=2009|publisher=[[RCA Records]]/[[19 Recordings]]}}</ref> [[Lesley Roy]],<ref name="KatyLesley">{{cite news|url=http://www.cbsnews.com/news/second-cup-cafe-lesley-roy/|title=Second Cup Cafe: Lesley Roy|last=Castellanos|first=Melissa|publisher=CBS News|date=September 26, 2008|accessdate=May 24, 2014|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140908070609/http://www.cbsnews.com/news/second-cup-cafe-lesley-roy/|archivedate=September 8, 2014}}</ref> [[Britney Spears]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1718479/britney-spears-katy-perry-britney-jean-passenger/|publisher=MTV News|title=Britney Spears Explains How 'Amazing' Katy Perry Ended Up On Britney Jean|date=December 4, 2013|accessdate=August 25, 2014|first=Christina|last=Garibaldi|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140826160950/http://www.mtv.com/news/1718479/britney-spears-katy-perry-britney-jean-passenger/|archivedate=August 26, 2014}}</ref> [[Iggy Azalea]],<ref>{{cite AV media notes|title=[[The New Classic]]|others=[[Iggy Azalea]]|year=2014|publisher=The Island Def Jam Music Group}}</ref> [[Ariana Grande]] and [[Nicki Minaj]].<ref>{{cite AV media notes|title=[[The Pinkprint]]|others=[[Nicki Minaj]]|year=2014|publisher=[[Universal Music Group]]}}</ref>

===Voice===
Perry has a [[contralto]] vocal range.<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Grewal|first=Samar|date=October 9, 2008|title=Review: Katy Perry&nbsp;– One of the Boys|url=http://rollingstoneindia.com/katy-perry-2/|magazine=Rolling Stone|accessdate=March 16, 2014|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140317031519/http://rollingstoneindia.com/katy-perry-2/|archivedate=March 17, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|title=Review: 'Katy Perry'|url=https://variety.com/2009/music/reviews/katy-perry-2-1200473923/|first=Steven|last=Mirkin|magazine=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=February 1, 2009|accessdate=March 16, 2014|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140317024708/http://variety.com/2009/music/reviews/katy-perry-2-1200473923/|archivedate=March 17, 2014}}</ref> Her singing has received both praise and criticism. Betty Clarke of ''[[The Guardian]]'' commented that her "powerful voice is hard-edged"<ref>{{cite news|last=Clarke|first=Betty|title=Katy Perry&nbsp;– review|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2013/oct/01/katy-perry-itunes-festival-review|newspaper=The Guardian|date=October 1, 2013|accessdate=February 5, 2014|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140223005639/http://www.theguardian.com/music/2013/oct/01/katy-perry-itunes-festival-review|archivedate=February 23, 2014}}</ref> while [[Rob Sheffield]] from ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' described Perry's vocals on ''Teenage Dream'' as "processed [[staccato]] blips".<ref name=SheffieldDream/> Darren Harvey of [[musicOMH]] compared Perry's vocals on ''One of the Boys'' to Alanis Morissette's, both possessing a "perky voice shifting octaves mid-syllable".<ref>{{cite web|last=Harvey|first=Darren|title=Katy Perry&nbsp;– One of the Boys|url=http://www.musicomh.com/reviews/albums/katy-perry-one-of-the-boys|work=[[musicOMH]]|date=September 15, 2008|accessdate=February 5, 2014|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140104212820/http://www.musicomh.com/reviews/albums/katy-perry-one-of-the-boys|archivedate=January 4, 2014}}</ref> Alex Miller from ''[[NME]]'' felt that "Perry's problem is often her voice" on ''One of the Boys'', stating that "somewhere along the line someone convinced her she was like, well, a ballsy rock chick".<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Miller|first=Alex|title=NME Album Reviews&nbsp;– Katy Perry|url=http://www.nme.com/reviews/9900|magazine=NME|accessdate=February 5, 2014|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140116104108/http://www.nme.com/reviews/9900|archivedate=January 16, 2014}}</ref> Conversely, Bernadette McNulty from ''[[The Daily Telegraph]]'' praised her "rock chick voice" in a review of a concert promoting ''Prism''.<ref>{{cite news|last=McNulty|first=Bernadette|title=Katy Perry, iTunes Festival, Roundhouse, review|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/music/live-music-reviews/10347052/Katy-Perry-iTunes-Festival-Roundhouse-review.html|newspaper=[[The Daily Telegraph]]|accessdate=February 5, 2014|date=October 1, 2013|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140322153914/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/music/live-music-reviews/10347052/Katy-Perry-iTunes-Festival-Roundhouse-review.html|archivedate=March 22, 2014}}</ref>

==Public image==
[[File:Katy Perry California Dreams Tour 01.jpg|thumb|upright|Perry's characteristic spinning peppermint swirl dress|alt=Perry performing in a dress decorated with peppermint swirls]]

Perry is considered a [[sex symbol]]; ''[[GQ]]'' labelled her a "full-on male fantasy",<ref name="GQ"/> while ''[[Elle (magazine)|Elle]]'' described her body "as though sketched by a teenage boy".<ref name="Elle"/> ''[[Vice (magazine)|Vice]]'' described her as a "'serious' popstar/woman/sex symbol".<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://noisey.vice.com/blog/does-madonna-need-katy-perry-more-than-katy-perry-needs-madonna|title=Does Madonna Need Katy Perry More Than Katy Perry Needs Madonna?|date=May 24, 2014|magazine=[[Vice (magazine)|Vice]]|first=Kat|last=George|accessdate=May 29, 2014|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140527231625/http://noisey.vice.com/blog/does-madonna-need-katy-perry-more-than-katy-perry-needs-madonna|archivedate=May 27, 2014}}</ref> She was placed at number one on the ''[[Maxim (magazine)|Maxim]]'' Hot 100 in 2010 as the "most beautiful woman in the world", with editor Joe Levy describing her as a "triple&nbsp;– no quadruple&nbsp;– kind of hot".<ref name=MaximHot100>{{cite news|title=Katy Perry tops Maxim's Hot 100 list|url=http://marquee.blogs.cnn.com/2010/05/10/katy-perry-tops-maxims-hot-100-list/|publisher=[[CNN]]|accessdate=October 21, 2014|date=May 10, 2010|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141022071906/http://marquee.blogs.cnn.com/2010/05/10/katy-perry-tops-maxims-hot-100-list/|archivedate=October 22, 2014}}</ref> ''[[Men's Health (magazine)|Men's Health]]'' readers voted her the "sexiest woman of 2013".<ref name="The Hottest Women of 2013 - Men's Health">{{cite magazine|url=http://www.menshealth.com/sex-women/hottest-women-2013|title=The Hottest Women of 2013|magazine=[[Men's Health (magazine)|Men's Health]]|date=January 2013|accessdate=April 29, 2014|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131114153615/http://www.menshealth.com/sex-women/hottest-women-2013|archivedate=November 14, 2013}}</ref> In November 2010, Perry told ''[[Harper's Bazaar]]'' that she was proud of and satisfied with her figure.<ref name=HarpersBazaar>{{cite magazine|last=Apodaca|first=Rose|title=Katy Perry's Interview&nbsp;– Quotes from Katy Perry|url=http://www.harpersbazaar.com/fashion/fashion-photography/katy-perry-interview-1210|magazine=[[Harper's Bazaar]]|accessdate=February 6, 2014|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140110082317/http://www.harpersbazaar.com/fashion/fashion-photography/katy-perry-interview-1210|archivedate=January 10, 2014}}</ref>

Perry's fashion often incorporates humor, bright colors, and food-related themes<ref>{{cite news|last=Larson|first=John|title=Katy Perry // "Teenage Dream"|url=http://www.tacomaweekly.com/citylife/view/katy_perry/|newspaper=[[Tacoma Weekly]]|accessdate=June 19, 2013|date=September 14, 2010|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131109082707/http://www.tacomaweekly.com/citylife/view/katy_perry/|archivedate=November 9, 2013}}</ref> such as her trademark spinning peppermint swirl dress.<ref name="pb5">{{cite magazine|last=Menyes|first=Carolyn|title=Katy Perry Asked to Ditch Hazardous Peppermint Bra|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/481674/katy-perry-asked-to-ditch-hazardous-peppermint-bra|magazine=Billboard|accessdate=June 19, 2013|date=July 12, 2012|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130529054945/http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/481674/katy-perry-asked-to-ditch-hazardous-peppermint-bra|archivedate=May 29, 2013}}</ref> ''[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]]'' described her as "never exactly one to shy away from the outrageous or the extreme in any realm",<ref>{{cite magazine|title=Fashion Fireworks: Katy Perry's Best Performance Looks|url=http://www.vogue.com/vogue-daily/article/fashion-fireworks-katy-perrys-best-performance-looks/#1|magazine=Vogue|accessdate=February 6, 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131221061713/http://www.vogue.com/vogue-daily/article/fashion-fireworks-katy-perrys-best-performance-looks/#1|archivedate=December 21, 2013}}</ref> while ''[[Glamour (magazine)|Glamour]]'' named her the "queen of quirk".<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Lyons Powell|first=Hannah|title=Katy Perry's Changing Style and Fashion|url=http://www.glamourmagazine.co.uk/fashion/celebrity-fashion/2010/08/katy-perry-craziest-fashion-and-style-ever#!image-number=23|magazine=Glamour|accessdate=February 6, 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140219033238/http://www.glamourmagazine.co.uk/fashion/celebrity-fashion/2010/08/katy-perry-craziest-fashion-and-style-ever#!image-number=23|archivedate=February 19, 2014|date=}}</ref> In February 2009, Perry told ''[[Seventeen (American magazine)|Seventeen]]'' that her fashion style was "a bit of a concoction of different things" and stated she enjoyed humor in her clothing.<ref name="17Style">{{cite magazine|url=http://www.seventeen.com/fashion/special/style-blog/katy-perry-fashion-qa-interview|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090908222401/http://www.seventeen.com/fashion/special/style-blog/katy-perry-fashion-qa-interview|title=Find Out What Influences Katy Perry's Cute Style!|date=February 5, 2009|magazine=[[Seventeen (American magazine)|Seventeen]]|accessdate=April 29, 2014|archivedate=September 8, 2009}}</ref> She has also described herself as having "[[Dissociative identity disorder|multipersonality disorder]]" for fashion.<ref name=HarpersBazaar/> Perry lists Gwen Stefani, [[Shirley Manson]], [[Chloë Sevigny]], [[Daphne Guinness]], [[Natalie Portman]], and the fictional character [[Lolita]] as her style icons.<ref name=WMag/><ref>{{cite news|last=Young|first=Katy|title=Katy Perry reveals her perfume preferences|url=http://fashion.telegraph.co.uk/beauty/news-features/TMG10347572/Katy-Perry-reveals-her-perfume-preferences.html|newspaper=The Daily Telegraph|accessdate=October 1, 2013|date=October 1, 2013|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131002154813/http://fashion.telegraph.co.uk/beauty/news-features/TMG10347572/Katy-Perry-reveals-her-perfume-preferences.html|archivedate=October 2, 2013}}</ref>

On social media, Perry surpassed [[Justin Bieber]] as the most followed person on [[Twitter]] in November 2013.<ref>{{cite news|first=Sean|last=Hollister|url=https://www.theverge.com/2013/11/3/5061834/katy-perry-passes-justin-bieber-as-most-popular-person-on-twitter|title=Katy Perry passes Justin Bieber as most popular person on Twitter|newspaper=[[The Verge]]|date=November 3, 2013|accessdate=November 4, 2013|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131104135526/http://www.theverge.com/2013/11/3/5061834/katy-perry-passes-justin-bieber-as-most-popular-person-on-twitter|archivedate=November 4, 2013}}</ref> She won the 2015 Guinness World Record for most Twitter followers,<ref name=Guinness2015>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/wherever-they-may-roam-metallica-set-guinness-world-record-for-touring-20140904|magazine=Rolling Stone|date=September 4, 2014|accessdate=September 4, 2014|first=Kory|last=Grow|title=Wherever They May Roam: Metallica Set Guinness World Record for Touring|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140905012331/http://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/wherever-they-may-roam-metallica-set-guinness-world-record-for-touring-20140904|archivedate=September 5, 2014}}</ref> and became the first person to gain 100 million followers on the site in June 2017.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/amp/news/katy-perry-becomes-first-hit-100-million-twitter-followers-1014285|date=June 16, 2017|accessdate=June 16, 2017|magazine=The Hollywood Reporter|first=Tatiana|last=Cirisano|title=Katy Perry Becomes First to Hit 100 Million Twitter Followers|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170616211605/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/amp/news/katy-perry-becomes-first-hit-100-million-twitter-followers-1014285|archivedate=June 16, 2017}}</ref> Keith Caulfield of ''Billboard'' stated that the singer is "the rare celebrity who seems to have enormous popularity but genuine ground-level interaction with her adoring KatyCats."<ref>{{cite news|last=Gundersen|first=Edna|title=Katy Perry tells how to 'tame the social media dragon'|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/music/2013/10/21/twitter-queen-katy-perry-offers-social-media-tips/3098961/|newspaper=USA Today|accessdate=February 7, 2014|date=October 21, 2013|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140205092732/http://www.usatoday.com/story/life/music/2013/10/21/twitter-queen-katy-perry-offers-social-media-tips/3098961/|archivedate=February 5, 2014}}</ref> With a combined total of over 246 million followers across [[Facebook]], [[Instagram]], and Twitter, she is the fourth most followed musician across social media.<ref>{{cite web|title=Music Fuels the Internet|url=http://www.musicfuels.com/|publisher=Recording Industry Association of America|date=January 2, 2018|accessdate=January 2, 2018}}</ref> In June 2017, ''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]'' listed Perry among its "25 Most Influential People on the Internet" of the year, writing that her live-stream for ''Witness'' was "blazing a trail" for being "the closest any major entertainer has come to giving fans the kind of 'real' intimacy that social media purports to provide".<ref>{{cite magazine|title=The 25 Most Influential People on the Internet|magazine=[[Time (magazine)|Time]]|date=June 26, 2017|url=http://time.com/4815217/most-influential-people-internet/|accessdate=June 27, 2017}}</ref>

In 2011, ''[[Forbes]]'' ranked Perry third on their "Top-Earning Women In Music" list with earnings of $44 million<ref name=Forbes2011>{{cite magazine|last=Greenburg|first=Zack O'Malley|authorlink=Zack O'Malley Greenburg|title=The Top-Earning Women In Music 2011|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/zackomalleygreenburg/2011/12/14/the-top-earning-women-in-music-lady-gaga-taylor-swift-katy-parry-alicia-keys/|magazine=[[Forbes]]|accessdate=December 14, 2011|date=December 14, 2011|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151027034418/http://www.forbes.com/sites/zackomalleygreenburg/2011/12/14/the-top-earning-women-in-music-lady-gaga-taylor-swift-katy-parry-alicia-keys/|archivedate=October 27, 2015}}</ref> and fifth on their 2012 list with $45 million.<ref name=Forbes2012>{{cite magazine|last=Greenburg|first=Zack O'Malley|title=The Top-Earning Women In Music 2012|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/zackomalleygreenburg/2012/12/12/the-top-earning-women-in-music-2012/|magazine=Forbes|accessdate=December 12, 2012|date=December 12, 2012|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121212223255/http://www.forbes.com/sites/zackomalleygreenburg/2012/12/12/the-top-earning-women-in-music-2012/|archivedate=December 12, 2012}}</ref> She subsequently ranked seventh on the 2013 ''Forbes'' list for "Top-Earning Women In Music" with $39 million earned,<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Greenburg|first=Zack O'Malley|title=The Top-Earning Women In Music 2013|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/zackomalleygreenburg/2013/12/11/the-top-earning-women-in-music-2013/|magazine=Forbes|accessdate=December 11, 2013|date=December 11, 2013|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://wayback.archive-it.org/all/20131215002555/http://www.forbes.com/sites/zackomalleygreenburg/2013/12/11/the-top-earning-women-in-music-2013/|archivedate=December 15, 2013}}</ref> and fifth on their 2014 list with $40 million.<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Greenburg|first=Zack O'Malley|title=The Top-Earning Women In Music 2014|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/zackomalleygreenburg/2014/11/04/the-top-earning-women-in-music-2014/|magazine=Forbes|accessdate=November 27, 2014|date=November 4, 2014|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141127085735/http://www.forbes.com/sites/zackomalleygreenburg/2014/11/04/the-top-earning-women-in-music-2014/|archivedate=November 27, 2014}}</ref> With earnings of $135 million, ''Forbes'' also ranked Perry number one on their 2015 "Top-Earning Women In Music" list as well as the "World's Highest-Paid Musicians" and declared her the highest earning female celebrity in 2015, placing her at number 3 on the ''Forbes'' Celebrity 100 list.<ref>2015 ''Forbes'' rankings:
* {{cite magazine|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/zackomalleygreenburg/2015/06/29/how-katy-perry-became-americas-top-pop-export-the-forbes-cover-story/|title=How Katy Perry Became America's Top Pop Export|last=Greenburg|first=Zack O'Malley|date=June 29, 2015|accessdate=June 30, 2015|work=Forbes|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150630073030/http://www.forbes.com/sites/zackomalleygreenburg/2015/06/29/how-katy-perry-became-americas-top-pop-export-the-forbes-cover-story/|archivedate=June 30, 2015}}
* {{cite magazine|last=Greenburg|first=Zack O'Malley|title=The World's Highest-Paid Women In Music 2015|journal=Forbes|date=November 4, 2015|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/zackomalleygreenburg/2015/11/04/the-worlds-highest-paid-women-in-music-2015/|accessdate=November 5, 2015|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151104161118/http://www.forbes.com/sites/zackomalleygreenburg/2015/11/04/the-worlds-highest-paid-women-in-music-2015/|archivedate=November 4, 2015}}
* {{cite magazine|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/zackomalleygreenburg/2015/12/08/the-worlds-highest-paid-musicians-of-2015/|journal=Forbes|date=December 8, 2015|accessdate=December 24, 2015|first=Zack O'Malley|last=Greenburg|title=The World's Highest-Paid Musicians Of 2015|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151225111722/http://www.forbes.com/sites/zackomalleygreenburg/2015/12/08/the-worlds-highest-paid-musicians-of-2015/|archivedate=December 25, 2015}}
</ref> In 2016, the magazine estimated her net worth was $125 million,<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/zackomalleygreenburg/2016/06/02/katy-perrys-net-worth-125-million-in-2016/|first=Zack O'Malley|last=Greenburg|date=June 2, 2016|accessdate=June 2, 2016|journal=Forbes|title=Katy Perry's Net Worth: $125 Million In 2016|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160602205724/http://www.forbes.com/sites/zackomalleygreenburg/2016/06/02/katy-perrys-net-worth-125-million-in-2016/|archivedate=June 2, 2016}}</ref> and ranked her number six on their list of "Highest-Paid Women in Music" with earnings of $41 million.<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Greenburg|first=Zack O'Malley|title=The World's Highest-Paid Women In Music 2016|journal=Forbes|date=November 2, 2016|url=https://www.forbes.com/pictures/eeel45fhghh/6-katy-perry-41-milli/#5dbe81824789|accessdate=November 4, 2016|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161104142659/http://www.forbes.com/pictures/eeel45fhghh/6-katy-perry-41-milli/|archivedate=November 4, 2016}}</ref> The following year, she was ranked number nine on the list with $33 million.<ref>{{cite magazine|last1=Greenburg|first1=Zack O'Malley|title=The World's Highest-Paid Women In Music 2017|magazine=Forbes|date=November 20, 2017|url=https://www.forbes.com/pictures/5a0c872a31358e286470082f/9-katy-perry-33-million/#7f0e1e643968|accessdate=November 22, 2017}}</ref> In 2018, she topped its "Highest-Paid Women in Music" listing and ranked at number four on the "Highest-Paid Female Celebrities" list with earnings of $83 million.<ref>{{cite magazine|last1=Cuccinello|first1=Hayley C.|title=Highest-Paid Women In Entertainment|magazine=Forbes|date=July 16, 2018|url=https://www.forbes.com/pictures/5b478cee31358e2c990ee2f9/4-katy-perry-83-million/#1fec95644839|accessdate=July 16, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|last1=Greenburg|first1=Zack O'Malley|title=The World's Highest-Paid Women In Music 2018|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/zackomalleygreenburg/2018/11/19/highest-paid-women-in-music-2018-katy-perry-taylor-swift-beyonce/|magazine=Forbes|date=November 19, 2018|accessdate=November 19, 2018}}</ref>

==Other ventures==

===Philanthropy===
[[File:Katy Perry UNICEF 2012.jpg|thumb|upright|Perry became a UNICEF Goodwill Ambassador in December 2013.|alt=Perry posing for photographers at a UNICEF gala]]

Perry has supported various charitable organizations and causes during her career. She has contributed to organizations aimed at improving the lives and welfare of children in particular. In April 2013, she joined [[UNICEF]] to assist children in Madagascar with education and nutrition.<ref>{{cite web|title=Katy Perry teams up with UNICEF and visits children in Madagascar|url=http://www.unicef.org/media/media_68612.html|publisher=[[UNICEF]]|accessdate=April 7, 2013|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130409235148/http://www.unicef.org/media/media_68612.html|archivedate=April 9, 2013}}</ref> On December 3, 2013, she was officially named a [[List of UNICEF Goodwill Ambassadors|UNICEF Goodwill Ambassador]], "with a special focus on engaging young people in the agency's work to improve the lives of the world's most vulnerable children and adolescents."<ref name=UNICEFGoodwillAmbassador>{{cite web|title=Katy Perry is UNICEF's newest Goodwill Ambassador|url=http://www.unicef.org/media/media_71241.html|publisher=UNICEF|date=December 3, 2013|accessdate=April 28, 2014|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140810104451/http://www.unicef.org/media/media_71241.html|archivedate=August 10, 2014}}</ref> She arranged for a portion of the money generated from tickets to her Prismatic World Tour to go to UNICEF.<ref name=PrismaticNorthAmerica>{{cite magazine|title=Katy Perry Cues Up 'Prismatic' World Tour|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/katy-perry-cues-up-prismatic-world-tour-20140115|magazine=Rolling Stone|date=January 15, 2014|last=Ryan|first=Reed|accessdate=April 28, 2014|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140331023510/http://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/katy-perry-cues-up-prismatic-world-tour-20140115|archivedate=March 31, 2014}}</ref> In September 2010, she helped build and design the Boys Hope/Girls Hope foundation shelter for youth in Baltimore, Maryland along with [[Raven-Symoné]], [[Shaquille O'Neal]], and the cast of ''[[Extreme Makeover: Home Edition]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Boys Hope/Girls Hope|publisher=[[American Broadcasting Company]]|url=http://abc.go.com/shows/extreme-makeover-home-edition/episode-guide/episode-801-boys-hope-girls-hope|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141018094040/http://abc.go.com/shows/extreme-makeover-home-edition/episode-guide/episode-801-boys-hope-girls-hope|accessdate=April 28, 2014|archivedate=October 18, 2014}}</ref>

She has also supported children's education and well-being. All profits from sales of the album ''The Gay Nineties Old Tyme Music: Daisy Bell'', which includes her rendition of "Daisy Bell (Bicycle Built for Two)", were donated to the charity [[Little Kids Rock]], which supports musical education in underprivileged elementary schools.<ref name=MarkRyder /> In June 2014, she teamed up with [[Staples Inc.]] for a project entitled "Make Roar Happen" which donated $1 million to [[DonorsChoose]], an organization that supports teachers and funds classroom resources in public schools.<ref>{{cite magazine|title=Katy Perry and Staples 'Make Roar Happen' to Help Support Teachers|first=Roy|last=Trakin|url=http://www.billboard.com/biz/articles/news/branding/6121146/katy-perry-and-staples-make-roar-happen-to-help-support-teachers|magazine=Billboard|date=June 12, 2014|accessdate=June 18, 2014|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140622012143/http://www.billboard.com/biz/articles/news/branding/6121146/katy-perry-and-staples-make-roar-happen-to-help-support-teachers|archivedate=June 22, 2014}}</ref> In May 2016, she worked with UNICEF to improve child care quality in Vietnam, hoping to "break the cycle of poverty and drastically improve children's health, education and well-being".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.unicef.org/media/media_91290.html|publisher=UNICEF|date=June 1, 2016|accessdate=June 2, 2016|title=UNICEF Goodwill Ambassador Katy Perry meets children facing immense challenges in Viet Nam|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160602122805/http://www.unicef.org/media/media_91290.html|archivedate=June 2, 2016}}</ref> The following month, UNICEF announced that Perry would receive the [[Audrey Hepburn]] Humanitarian Award "for her work as a UNICEF Goodwill Ambassador in support of the world's most vulnerable children" at their annual Snowflake Ball in November.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.unicefusa.org/press/releases/2016-unicef-snowflake-ball-honor-unicef-goodwill-ambassador-katy-perry-and|publisher=UNICEF|date=June 23, 2016|accessdate=June 23, 2016|title=2016 UNICEF Snowflake Ball to Honor UNICEF Goodwill Ambassador Katy Perry and Philanthropist Moll Anderson|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160817124534/https://www.unicefusa.org/press/releases/2016-unicef-snowflake-ball-honor-unicef-goodwill-ambassador-katy-perry-and|archivedate=August 17, 2016}}</ref>

Perry has supported organizations aimed at aiding people suffering with diseases including [[cancer]] and [[HIV/AIDS]]. During the 2008 Warped Tour, she had a cast made of her breasts to raise money for the [[Keep A Breast Foundation]].<ref>{{cite web|title=The Keep A Breast Foundation|url=http://www.keep-a-breast.org/breast-cast-art/history/|accessdate=May 20, 2014|publisher=[[Keep A Breast Foundation]]|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140330175940/http://keep-a-breast.org/breast-cast-art/history/|archivedate=March 30, 2014|df=}}</ref> She hosted and performed at the We Can Survive concert along with [[Bonnie McKee]], [[Kacey Musgraves]], [[Sara Bareilles]], [[Ellie Goulding]], and duo [[Tegan and Sara]] at the Hollywood Bowl in Los Angeles, California, on October 23, 2013. The concert's profits were donated to [[Young Survival Coalition]], an organization aiding [[breast cancer]] in young women.<ref name="Hollywood Bowl">{{cite magazine|last=Aguila|first=Justino|title=Katy Perry Hosts Famous Friends, Previews Next Tour at Hollywood Bowl: Live Review|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/5770379/katy-perry-hosts-famous-friends-previews-next-tour-at-hollywood|magazine=Billboard|date=October 24, 2013|accessdate=April 28, 2014|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140624200053/http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/5770379/katy-perry-hosts-famous-friends-previews-next-tour-at-hollywood|archivedate=June 24, 2014}}</ref> In June 2009, she designed an item of clothing for [[H&M]]'s "Fashion Against AIDS" campaign, which raises money for HIV/AIDS awareness projects.<ref>{{cite news|last=Vena|first=Jocelyn|title=Katy Perry, Tokio Hotel Join H&M for Fashion Against AIDS|url=http://newsroom.mtv.com/2009/05/06/katy-perry-tokio-hotel-join-hm-for-fashion-against-aids/|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090508092144/http://newsroom.mtv.com/2009/05/06/katy-perry-tokio-hotel-join-hm-for-fashion-against-aids/|dead-url=yes|archive-date=May 8, 2009|publisher=MTV News|accessdate=March 14, 2014}}</ref> On February 26, 2017, she served as a co-chair alongside various celebrities such as [[Beyoncé]], [[Lea Michele]], [[Jim Carrey]], [[Jared Leto]], and [[Kevin Spacey]] for the 25th Annual [[Elton John AIDS Foundation Academy Award Party]], a fundraiser for HIV/AIDS healthcare.<ref>{{cite web|title=EJAF's 25th Annual Academy Awards Viewing Party: Sunday, February 26, 2017|url=http://newyork.ejaf.org/ejafs-25th-annual-academy-awards-viewing-party-sunday-february-26-2017/|publisher=[[Elton John AIDS Foundation]]|accessdate=January 18, 2017}}</ref>

The proceeds from Perry's single "Part of Me" were donated to the charity [[MusiCares]], which helps musicians in times of need.<ref>{{cite news|title=Katy Perry donates proceeds from new single to charity|url=https://news.yahoo.com/katy-perry-donates-proceeds-single-charity-191441877.html|date=February 16, 2012|publisher=[[Yahoo! News]]|accessdate=May 25, 2014|first=Alexandra|last=Myers|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140715030356/http://news.yahoo.com/katy-perry-donates-proceeds-single-charity-191441877.html|archivedate=July 15, 2014}}</ref> During her California Dreams Tour, she raised over $175,000 for the Tickets-For-Charity fundraiser. The money was divided between three charities: the [[Children's Health Fund]] (CHF), Generosity Water, and [[The Humane Society of the United States]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.childrenshealthfund.org/sites/default/files/Katy-Perry-TFC-Check-Presenation.pdf|title=Katy Perry Celebrates Over $175K Raised for Charity on Her California Dreams Tour through Tickets-for-Charity|publisher=[[Children's Health Fund]]|date=December 8, 2011|accessdate=April 28, 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150923202756/http://www.childrenshealthfund.org/sites/default/files/Katy-Perry-TFC-Check-Presenation.pdf|archivedate=September 23, 2015}}</ref> On her 27th birthday, Perry set up a donations page for the [[Society for the Prevention of Cruelty to Animals]] Auckland,<ref>{{cite web|title=Katy Perry Asks For Charity Donations To Mark Birthday|url=http://www.contactmusic.com/news/katy-perry-asks-for-charity-donations-to-mark-birthday_1252678|publisher=Contactmusic.com. Channel 4|date=October 26, 2011|accessdate=November 11, 2011|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111028202414/http://www.contactmusic.com/news/katy-perry-asks-for-charity-donations-to-mark-birthday_1252678|archivedate=October 28, 2011}}</ref> and set up a similar page benefiting the [[David Lynch Foundation]] for her 28th birthday.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Davidson|first1=Danica|title=Sweet Treat: Katy Perry asks for Charitable Donations for her 28th Birthday|url=http://act.mtv.com/posts/sweet-tweet-katy-perry-donations-birthday/|publisher=MTV|accessdate=June 27, 2014|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714162901/http://act.mtv.com/posts/sweet-tweet-katy-perry-donations-birthday/|archivedate=July 14, 2014}}</ref> On March 29, 2014, she helped raise $2.4 million for the [[Museum of Contemporary Art, Los Angeles|Museum of Contemporary Art]] in Los Angeles along with other celebrities such as [[Ryan Seacrest]], [[Pharrell Williams]], [[Tim Allen]], [[Lisa Edelstein]], and [[Riley Keough]].<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/6029354/katy-perry-pharrell-williams-help-raise-24-million-for-moca|first=Tina|last=Daunt|title=Katy Perry, Pharrell Williams Help Raise $2.4 Million for MOCA|magazine=Billboard|date=March 31, 2014|accessdate=April 10, 2014|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140403054200/http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/6029354/katy-perry-pharrell-williams-help-raise-24-million-for-moca|archivedate=April 3, 2014}}</ref> In March 2018, Perry announced ''Witness: Coming Home'', a benefit concert that was held in her hometown of Santa Barbara, California on May 19, 2018. The concert benefited those recovering from the aftermath of the [[2017 California wildfires]] and [[2018 Southern California mudflows]]. Perry partnered with the Santa Barbara Foundation, the 93108 Fund and The 805 UndocuFund, organizations which help in assisting members of the community in the Santa Barbara area through grants and various philanthropic efforts.<ref name="WitnessComingHome">{{cite web|last1=Shackleford|first1=Tom|title=Katy Perry announces Witness: Coming Home benefit show at the Santa Barbara Bowl|work=AXS|date=March 13, 2018|url=https://www.axs.com/katy-perry-announces-witness-coming-home-benefit-show-at-the-santa-bar-128822|accessdate=March 19, 2018}}</ref>

Perry performed at the [[One Love Manchester]] benefit concert for the victims of the [[2017 Manchester Arena bombing]] amongst various other performers including its organizer [[Ariana Grande]], which was broadcast live on June 4, 2017 through radio and various television stations throughout the world.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-40134567|title=One Love Manchester: What you need to know|date=June 4, 2017|publisher=BBC News|accessdate=June 4, 2017|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170604022705/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-40134567|archivedate=June 4, 2017}}</ref>

===Politics===
[[File:Katy Perry Hillary Clinton, I%27m With Her Concert.jpg|thumb|upright|left|Perry performed at multiple ceremonies for Democratic presidential candidate Hillary Clinton during her 2016 campaign.|alt=Hillary Clinton and Perry pose with hands connected at a fundraising concert]]
Perry has publicly advocated for [[LGBT rights in the United States|LGBT rights]]. She supported [[Stonewall (charity)|Stonewall]] during their "It gets better..... today" campaign to prevent [[homophobia|homophobic]] bullying,<ref>{{cite web|title=High profile support: Other messages|url=http://www.stonewall.org.uk/what_you_can_do/campaigning_opportunities/it_gets_better_today/4845.asp|publisher=[[Stonewall (charity)|Stonewall]]|date=November 17, 2010|accessdate=March 13, 2014|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150414145258/http://www.stonewall.org.uk/what_you_can_do/campaigning_opportunities/it_gets_better_today/4845.asp|archivedate=April 14, 2015}}</ref> and dedicated the music video to her song "Firework" to the [[It Gets Better Project]].<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/viral-videos/952410/katy-perry-dedicates-leaked-firework-video-to-lgbt-campaign|title=Katy Perry Dedicates Leaked 'Firework' Video to LGBT Campaign|magazine=Billboard|date=October 28, 2010|first=Jillian|last=Mapes|accessdate=April 28, 2014|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150719045440/http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/viral-videos/952410/katy-perry-dedicates-leaked-firework-video-to-lgbt-campaign|archivedate=July 19, 2015}}</ref> Perry told [[Do Something]] in November 2008 she was proud to be a LGBT rights activist, saying "I've always been a very open-minded person, but I definitely believe in equality." She confirmed that she voted against [[California Proposition 8 (2008)|Proposition 8]], an amendment (ultimately ruled unconstitutional) that legally defined marriage as a union solely between a man and a woman in [[California]].<ref name="DoSomething">{{cite web|url=http://www.dosomething.org/page/katy-perry-talks-about-gay-rights-interview-with-cgg|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006153308/https://www.dosomething.org/page/katy-perry-talks-about-gay-rights-interview-with-cgg|archivedate=October 6, 2014|title=Katy Perry talks about gay rights in interview with CGG|publisher=[[Do Something]]|date=November 4, 2008|accessdate=November 5, 2011}}</ref> In June 2012, Perry expressed her hopes for LGBT equality, commenting "hopefully, we will look back at this moment and think like we do now concerning [other] [[Civil and political rights|civil rights]] issues. We'll just shake our heads in disbelief, saying, 'Thank God we've evolved.' That would be my prayer for the future."<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Hauser|first=Brooke|title=Katy Perry Celebrates Her Independence|url=http://parade.condenast.com/31418/brookehauser/28-katy-perry-part-of-me/|magazine=[[Parade (magazine)|Parade]]|date=June 28, 2012|accessdate=February 6, 2014|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140221233214/http://parade.condenast.com/31418/brookehauser/28-katy-perry-part-of-me/|archivedate=February 21, 2014}}</ref> In December 2012, Perry was awarded the Trevor Hero Award by [[The Trevor Project]] for her work and activism on behalf of LGBT youth.<ref name="TrevorHero">{{cite web|title=Katy Perry Accepts Hero Award From Trevor Project|url=http://www.contactmusic.com/news/katy-perry-accepts-hero-award-from-trevor-project_3399852|publisher=Contactmusic.com|date=December 3, 2012|accessdate=April 28, 2014|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140712160546/http://www.contactmusic.com/news/katy-perry-accepts-hero-award-from-trevor-project_3399852|archivedate=July 12, 2014}}</ref> On March 18, 2017, she received a Nation Equality Award from [[Human Rights Campaign]] for "using her powerful voice and international platform to speak out for LGBTQ equality", with the organization further stating that "Katy's message of inclusion and equality continues to inspire us and the world".<ref>{{cite magazine|last1=Gardner|first1=Chris|title=Katy Perry, America Ferrera and Senator Tim Kaine Set to Appear at HRC Gala|magazine=The Hollywood Reporter|date=March 9, 2017|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/katy-perry-america-ferrera-senator-tim-kaine-set-appear-at-hrc-gala-984835|accessdate=March 11, 2017|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170311013053/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/katy-perry-america-ferrera-senator-tim-kaine-set-appear-at-hrc-gala-984835|archivedate=March 11, 2017}}</ref>

Perry describes herself as a [[feminism|feminist]],<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Stampler|first=Laura|title=Katy Perry: Maybe I am a Feminist After All|url=http://time.com/28554/katy-perry-feminist-after-all-confused/|magazine=[[Time (magazine)|Time]]|date=March 18, 2014|accessdate=June 16, 2014|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140615032440/http://time.com/28554/katy-perry-feminist-after-all-confused/|archivedate=June 15, 2014}}</ref> and appeared in April 2013 in a video clip for the "Chime For Change" campaign that aimed to spread female empowerment.<ref>{{cite magazine|title=Watch: Beyoncé, Blake Lively, Katy Perry, and More Unite in Chime for Change Video|url=http://www.elle.com/news/fashion-style/beyonce-blake-lively-katy-perry-chime-for-change-video|first=Lauren|last=Levinson|magazine=Elle|accessdate=April 28, 2014|date=April 16, 2013|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140630135325/http://www.elle.com/news/fashion-style/beyonce-blake-lively-katy-perry-chime-for-change-video|archivedate=June 30, 2014}}</ref> She has also said that America's lack of free [[Health care in the United States|health care]] drove her "absolutely crazy".<ref>{{cite magazine|title=Katy Perry Talks Body Image, Fame, and Politics in Rolling Stone Cover Story|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/katy-perry-talks-body-image-fame-and-politics-in-rolling-stone-cover-story-20110622|magazine=Rolling Stone|date=June 22, 2011|accessdate=February 16, 2014|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140307074611/http://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/katy-perry-talks-body-image-fame-and-politics-in-rolling-stone-cover-story-20110622|archivedate=March 7, 2014}}</ref> Following the [[2016 Orlando nightclub shooting|shooting at the Pulse nightclub in Orlando]] in June 2016, Perry and nearly 200 other artists and executives in music signed an open letter organized by ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' addressed to [[United States Congress]] demanding increased [[gun control]] in the United States.<ref>{{cite magazine|title=An Open Letter to Congress from the Music Industry|journal=Billboard|date=June 23, 2016|url=http://www.billboard.com/open-letter/|accessdate=June 23, 2016|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160624111250/http://www.billboard.com/open-letter/|archivedate=June 24, 2016}}</ref>

Through Twitter and by performing at his rallies, Perry supported President [[Barack Obama]] in his run for re-election and praised his support for [[Same-sex marriage in the United States|same-sex marriage]]<ref name=bamanails>{{cite news|last=Porter|first=Amber|title=Katy Perry Nails it for Obama|url=http://abcnews.go.com/blogs/politics/2012/10/katy-perry-nails-it-for-obama/|date=October 8, 2012|publisher=ABC News|accessdate=November 4, 2012|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121012020542/http://abcnews.go.com/blogs/politics/2012/10/katy-perry-nails-it-for-obama/|archivedate=October 12, 2012}}</ref> and LGBT equality.<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Strecker|first=Erin|title=Katy Perry performing another free concert at Obama rally|url=http://music-mix.ew.com/2012/11/01/katy-perry-milwaukee-president-obama/|magazine=Entertainment Weekly|date=November 1, 2012|accessdate=November 4, 2012|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121105002311/http://music-mix.ew.com/2012/11/01/katy-perry-milwaukee-president-obama/|archivedate=November 5, 2012}}</ref> She performed at three rallies for Obama, in Los Angeles, Las Vegas, and Wisconsin, singing a rendition of "[[Let's Stay Together (Al Green song)|Let's Stay Together]]" as well as a number of her songs. During her Las Vegas performance she wore a dress made to replicate a voting ballot, with Obama's box filled in.<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Strecker|first=Erin|title=Katy Perry performs at third President Obama rally in Wisconsin|url=http://music-mix.ew.com/2012/11/01/katy-perry-milwaukee-president-obama/|magazine=Entertainment Weekly|accessdate=February 9, 2014|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140205082103/http://music-mix.ew.com/2012/11/01/katy-perry-milwaukee-president-obama/|archivedate=February 5, 2014}}</ref> On Twitter, she encouraged her followers to vote for Obama.<ref>{{cite web|last=Nessif|first=Bruna|title=K2012 Election: Katy Perry, George Lopez, Rashida Jones, and More Take to Twitter to Get Out the Vote|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/360412/2012-election-katy-perry-george-lopez-rashida-jones-and-more-take-to-twitter-to-get-out-the-vote|publisher=E!|accessdate=February 16, 2014|date=November 5, 2012|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140425053240/http://www.eonline.com/news/360412/2012-election-katy-perry-george-lopez-rashida-jones-and-more-take-to-twitter-to-get-out-the-vote|archivedate=April 25, 2014}}</ref>

In August 2013, Perry voiced criticism of [[Tony Abbott]], then-leader of conservative [[Liberal Party of Australia]] and candidate for [[Prime Minister of Australia]], due to his opposition to gay marriage and told Abbott, "I love you as a human being but I can't give you my vote."<ref name="TonyAbbott">{{cite news|title=Katy Perry confronts Tony Abbott on gay marriage|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/australiaandthepacific/australia/10243985/Katy-Perry-confronts-Tony-Abbott-on-gay-marriage.html|newspaper=The Daily Telegraph|accessdate=February 6, 2014|date=August 15, 2013|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140322153911/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/australiaandthepacific/australia/10243985/Katy-Perry-confronts-Tony-Abbott-on-gay-marriage.html|archivedate=March 22, 2014}}</ref> In April 2014, she publicly supported [[Marianne Williamson]] in her campaign for [[California's 33rd congressional district]] by attending a political press event.<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Schwiegershausen|first=Erica|title=Katy Perry Exposed a Springy Strip of Upper Belly|url=http://nymag.com/thecut/2014/04/katy-perry-exposed-a-springy-strip-of-belly.html|magazine=[[New York (magazine)|New York]]|accessdate=April 9, 2014|date=April 9, 2014|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140411161354/http://nymag.com/thecut/2014/04/katy-perry-exposed-a-springy-strip-of-belly.html|archivedate=April 11, 2014}}</ref> She endorsed [[Kamala Harris]] in the [[United States Senate election in California, 2016|United States Senate election in California]], and organized a fundraiser for Harris at her home in Los Angeles in November 2016.<ref>{{cite magazine|title=Katy Perry's Fundraiser For Kamala Harris|url=http://www.wmagazine.com/gallery/katy-perry-kamala-harris/all|magazine=[[W (magazine)|W]]|accessdate=November 10, 2016|date=November 6, 2016|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161111061053/http://www.wmagazine.com/gallery/katy-perry-kamala-harris/all|archivedate=November 11, 2016}}</ref> Perry also publicly endorsed former [[United States Secretary of State|Secretary of State]] [[Hillary Clinton]] for president in [[United States presidential election, 2016|2016]].<ref>{{Cite magazine|title=Katy Perry Offers to Write Hillary Clinton Campaign Theme Song|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/earshot/katy-perry-offers-write-hillary-713915|date=June 22, 2014|accessdate=August 21, 2015|work=The Hollywood Reporter|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151117141708/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/earshot/katy-perry-offers-write-hillary-713915|archivedate=November 17, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|title=Celebs show they are ready for Hillary by embracing her logo|url=http://www.msnbc.com/msnbc/celebs-show-they-are-ready-hillary-embracing-her-logo|publisher=[[MSNBC]]|first=Bridget|last=Todd|date=June 13, 2015|accessdate=August 21, 2015|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150816132122/http://www.msnbc.com/msnbc/celebs-show-they-are-ready-hillary-embracing-her-logo|archivedate=August 16, 2015}}</ref> She performed alongside [[Elton John]] at a fundraising concert for Clinton in [[New York City]] in March 2016.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Claiborne|first1=Matthew|title=Katy Perry, Elton John Perform at Hillary Clinton Fundraiser In New York|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Politics/katy-perry-elton-john-perform-hillary-clinton-fundraiser/story?id=37359679|accessdate=June 3, 2016|publisher=ABC News|date=March 3, 2016|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160610093149/http://abcnews.go.com/Politics/katy-perry-elton-john-perform-hillary-clinton-fundraiser/story?id=37359679|archivedate=June 10, 2016}}</ref> Perry also spoke and performed at the [[2016 Democratic National Convention]] in support of Clinton.<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Grant|first=Sarah|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/politics/news/watch-katy-perry-rise-and-roar-for-hillary-clinton-at-dnc-w431537|title=Watch Katy Perry 'Rise' and 'Roar' for Hillary Clinton at DNC|journal=Rolling Stone|date=July 28, 2016|accessdate=July 29, 2016|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160730152403/http://www.rollingstone.com/politics/news/watch-katy-perry-rise-and-roar-for-hillary-clinton-at-dnc-w431537|archivedate=July 30, 2016}}</ref>
<!-- ===Property===
Perry's attempted purchase of a former convent in [[Los Feliz]] resulted in acrimony and legal action, with one of the nuns from the convent claiming, "It would be a sin to sell to her."<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2018/mar/11/nun-dies-in-court-while-fighting-convent-sale-to-katy-perry|title=Nun dies in court while fighting convent sale to Katy Perry|first=|last=Reuters|date=March 11, 2018|website=the Guardian}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.npr.org/sections/thetwo-way/2018/03/10/592623697/nun-involved-in-katy-perry-convent-lawsuit-collapses-and-dies-in-court|title=Nun Involved In Katy Perry Convent Lawsuit Collapses And Dies In Court|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://laist.com/2015/06/30/photos_katy_perry_wants_to_buy_this.php|title=Photos: Inside The Los Feliz Convent Katy Perry Wants To Buy|publisher=|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180311020657/http://laist.com/2015/06/30/photos_katy_perry_wants_to_buy_this.php|archivedate=March 11, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://abc7.com/news/katy-perry-battling-nuns-in-bid-to-buy-former-convent-in-los-feliz/816887/|title=Katy Perry battling nuns in bid to buy former convent in Los Feliz|first=Miriam Hernandez, bio,|last=about|date=June 30, 2015|publisher=}}</ref>
