==Achievements==
{{See also|List of awards and nominations received by Katy Perry}}
[[File:Katy Perry (15262665623).jpg|thumb|upright|Perry  at the [[ARIA Music Awards]] in November 2014]]
Throughout her career, Perry has won five American Music Awards,<ref>American Music Awards for Katy Perry:
* {{cite news|last=Dinh|first=James|title=Katy Perry Strips Down 'One That Got Away' At AMAs|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1674725/katy-perry-amas.jhtml|accessdate=April 26, 2014|publisher=MTV News|date=November 20, 2011|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140427013448/http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1674725/katy-perry-amas.jhtml|archivedate=April 27, 2014}}
* {{cite magazine|title=AMAs 2012: Full Winners List|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/474103/amas-2012-full-winners-list|magazine=Billboard|accessdate=April 26, 2014|date=November 18, 2012|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140621011938/http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/474103/amas-2012-full-winners-list|archivedate=June 21, 2014}}
* {{cite news|title=One Direction, Katy Perry win big at American Music Awards|date=November 23, 2014|url=https://www.bostonglobe.com/arts/2014/11/23/one-direction-katy-perry-win-big-american-music-awards/jvPZILs9TXJxyK17CubtTJ/story.html|accessdate=November 23, 2014|newspaper=The Boston Globe|first=Mesfin|last=Fekadu|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141129060611/http://www.bostonglobe.com/arts/2014/11/23/one-direction-katy-perry-win-big-american-music-awards/jvPZILs9TXJxyK17CubtTJ/story.html|archivedate=November 29, 2014}}</ref> fourteen [[People's Choice Awards]],<ref>People's Choice Awards for Katy Perry:
* {{cite web|title=People's Choice Awards 2009 Nominees|url=http://www.peopleschoice.com/pca/awards/nominees/index.jsp?year=2009|publisher=[[CBS]]|accessdate=April 27, 2014|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091027004716/http://www.peopleschoice.com/pca/awards/nominees/index.jsp?year=2009|archivedate=October 27, 2009}}
* {{cite web|title=People's Choice Awards 2011 Nominees|url=http://www.peopleschoice.com/pca/awards/nominees/index.jsp?year=2011|publisher=CBS|accessdate=April 27, 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6CXuR4pK5?url=http://www.peopleschoice.com/pca/awards/nominees/index.jsp?year=2011|archivedate=November 29, 2012|df=}}
* {{cite web|title=People's Choice Awards 2012 Nominees|url=http://www.peopleschoice.com/pca/awards/nominees/index.jsp?year=2012|publisher=CBS|accessdate=April 27, 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120109013135/http://www.peopleschoice.com/pca/awards/nominees/index.jsp?year=2012|archivedate=January 9, 2012|df=}}
* {{cite web|title=People's Choice Awards 2013 Nominees|url=http://www.peopleschoice.com/pca/awards/nominees/index.jsp?year=2013|publisher=CBS|accessdate=April 27, 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160128023759/http://www.peopleschoice.com/pca/awards/nominees/index.jsp?year=2013|archivedate=January 28, 2016|df=}}
* {{cite web|title=People's Choice Awards 2014 Nominees|url=http://www.peopleschoice.com/pca/awards/nominees/index.jsp?year=2014|publisher=CBS|accessdate=April 27, 2014|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140112011024/http://www.peopleschoice.com/pca/awards/nominees/index.jsp?year=2014|archivedate=January 12, 2014}}</ref> four Guinness World Records,<ref name=Guinness2010/><ref name=Guinness2013/><ref name=Guinness2016/><ref name=Guinness2015/> a [[Brit Award]],<ref name=Brit2009/> and a [[Juno Award]].<ref name=Juno2011/> In September 2012, ''Billboard'' dubbed her the "Woman of the Year".<ref name=WomanOfTheYear/> From May 2010 to September 2011, the singer spent a record-breaking total of 69 consecutive weeks in the top ten of the ''Billboard'' Hot 100.<ref name="adeles-someone"/><ref name="billboardhot100perrycelebrates">{{cite magazine|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/471606/katy-perry-celebrates-year-in-hot-100s-top-10|title=Katy Perry Celebrates Year in Hot 100's Top 10|first=Gary|last=Trust|date=May 12, 2011|accessdate=May 13, 2011|magazine=Billboard|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110512203043/http://www.billboard.com/|archivedate=May 12, 2011}}</ref> ''Teenage Dream'' became the first album by a female artist to produce five number-one ''Billboard'' Hot 100 singles, and the second album overall after Michael Jackson's ''Bad''.<ref name=TieMichael/> In the United States, she has accumulated a total of nine number-one singles on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100, her most recent being "Dark Horse",<ref name=NumberOneHorse/> and holds the record for having 18 consecutive number-one songs on the [[Dance Club Songs]] chart.<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Murray|first=Gordon|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/7865881/katy-perry-swish-swish-dance-club-songs-number-one|title=Another One in the Basket: Katy Perry Nets 18th Club No. 1 With 'Swish Swish'|magazine=Billboard|date=July 13, 2017|accessdate=September 27, 2017}}</ref> ''Billboard'' also named her the 15th most successful dance club artist of all time.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/greatest-top-dance-club-artists|magazine=Billboard|title=Greatest of All Time Top Dance Club Artists|accessdate=September 27, 2017}}</ref> The magazine additionally ranked her 4th on its "Greatest of All Time Pop Songs Artists" list,<ref>{{cite magazine|title=Greatest of All Time Pop Songs Artists|magazine=Billboard|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/greatest-of-all-time-pop-songs-artists|accessdate=January 3, 2018}}</ref> included ''Teenage Dream'' and ''Prism'' among its "Greatest of All Time ''Billboard 200'' Albums by Women" list,<ref>{{cite magazine|title=Greatest of All Time Billboard 200 Albums by Women|magazine=Billboard|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/greatest-billboard-200-albums-by-women|accessdate=January 3, 2018}}</ref> and ranked "Dark Horse" at number 100 on its "Greatest of All Time Hot 100 Songs"<ref>{{cite magazine|title=Greatest of All Time Hot 100 Songs|magazine=Billboard|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/greatest-hot-100-singles|accessdate=January 3, 2018}}</ref> as well as one of its "Greatest of All Time Hot 100 Songs by Women" along with "E.T.", "Firework", and "California Gurls".<ref>{{cite magazine|title=Greatest of All Time Hot 100 Songs by Women|magazine=Billboard|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/greatest-hot-100-songs-by-women|accessdate=January 3, 2018}}</ref> In June 2015, her music video for "Dark Horse" became the first video by a female artist to reach 1 billion views on Vevo.<ref>{{cite magazine|title=Katy Perry's 'Dark Horse' Passes 1 Billion Vevo Views|first=Erin|last=Strecker|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/6590902/katy-perry-dark-horse-1-billion-vevo-views|magazine=Billboard|date=June 10, 2015|accessdate=June 10, 2015|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150612233806/http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/6590902/katy-perry-dark-horse-1-billion-vevo-views|archivedate=June 12, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Katy Perry Just Beat Taylor Swift To A Huge Milestone|first=Gil|last=Kaufman|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/2181184/katy-perry-dark-horse-billion-video-taylor-swift/|publisher=MTV News|date=June 9, 2015|accessdate=June 9, 2015|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150610090021/http://www.mtv.com/news/2181184/katy-perry-dark-horse-billion-video-taylor-swift/|archivedate=June 10, 2015}}</ref> The following month, her music video for "Roar" reached 1 billion views on Vevo, making her the first artist to have multiple videos with 1 billion views.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.iheart.com/articles/trending-104650/katy-perrys-roar-video-surpasses-1-13752984/|title=Katy Perry's 'Roar' Video Surpasses 1 Billion Vevo Views|publisher=[[iHeartRadio]]|date=July 10, 2015|accessdate=August 6, 2015|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150923181910/http://news.iheart.com/articles/trending-104650/katy-perrys-roar-video-surpasses-1-13752984/|archivedate=September 23, 2015}}</ref>

Perry was declared the Top Global Female Recording Artist of 2013 by the International Federation of the Phonographic Industry (IFPI).<ref name=IFPI/> According to Recording Industry Association of America (RIAA), she is the fifth [[List of highest-certified music artists in the United States|top digital singles artist]] in the United States, with 98 million certified song units in the country including on-demand streams<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.riaa.com/gold-platinum/?tab_active=top_tallies&ttt=TAS#search_section|title=Top Artists (Digital Singles)|publisher=Recording Industry Association of America|accessdate=August 21, 2015|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160126081620/http://www.riaa.com/gold-platinum/?tab_active=top_tallies&ttt=TAS|archivedate=January 26, 2016}}</ref> and also has 6 million certified album units, totaling 104 million certified units in the nation.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.riaa.com/gold-platinum/?tab_active=default-award&ar=katy+perry&ti=&lab=&genre=&format=Album&date_option=release&from=&to=&award=&type=&category=&adv=SEARCH#search_section|title=Katy Perry Album Certifications|publisher=Recording Industry Association of America|accessdate=February 12, 2018}}</ref> She also became the first artist to have three songs receive Diamond certifications from the RIAA with "Dark Horse", "Firework", and "Roar".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.riaa.com/katy-perry-makes-gold-platinum-history/|title=Katy Perry Makes Gold & Platinum History|publisher=Recording Industry Association of America|date=June 21, 2017|accessdate=June 22, 2017}}</ref> All three of them and "E.T.", "California Gurls", and "Hot n Cold" have each sold over 5 million digital copies.<ref name=Sales>{{cite web|last=Grein|first=Paul|title=MJ Makes Hot 100 History|url=https://music.yahoo.com/blogs/chart-watch/chart-watch-mj-makes-hot-100-history-225547952.html|publisher=Yahoo! Music|date=May 21, 2014|accessdate=May 21, 2014|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140522043849/https://music.yahoo.com/blogs/chart-watch/chart-watch-mj-makes-hot-100-history-225547952.html|archivedate=May 22, 2014}}</ref> Throughout her career, Perry has sold more than 40 million albums <ref>{{cite magazine|last=Wade|first=Cleo|url=https://www.glamour.com/story/katy-perry-march-2018-cover-story|title=Katy Perry: 'I Don't Want to Hold On to Childhood Trauma Anymore'|magazine=Glamour|date=February 6, 2018|accessdate=February 6, 2018}}</ref> and over 100 million records globally,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.uk/how-katy-perry-became-most-followed-celebrity-twitter-92-7-million-fans-1581149|title=How Katy Perry became the most-followed celebrity on Twitter with 92.7 million fans|work=International Business Times|first=Alicia|last=Adejobi|date=September 13, 2016|accessdate=September 15, 2016|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160914162208/http://www.ibtimes.co.uk/how-katy-perry-became-most-followed-celebrity-twitter-92-7-million-fans-1581149|archivedate=September 14, 2016}}</ref> making her [[List of best-selling music artists|one of the best-selling music artists of all time]].<ref>{{cite magazine|last=McIntyre|first=Hugh|title=Katy Perry Just Hit 90 Million Twitter Followers. Is 100 Million Coming Soon?|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/hughmcintyre/2016/07/01/katy-perry-is-now-the-first-person-to-hit-90-million-followers-on-twitter/|date=July 1, 2016|accessdate=July 2, 2016|magazine=Forbes|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160701234752/http://www.forbes.com/sites/hughmcintyre/2016/07/01/katy-perry-is-now-the-first-person-to-hit-90-million-followers-on-twitter/|archivedate=July 1, 2016}}</ref>

