{{MedalGold| [[2002 European Amateur Boxing Championships|2002 Perm]] | Bantamweight}}
{{MedalBottom}}

'''Khavazhi Khatsigov''' (born 17 April 1977 in [[Grozny]]) is a [[Boxing|boxer]] from [[Belarus]].

He was born in Russia, but after his failure to join the Russian national team ([[Raimkul Malakhbekov]] was the No.1 Russian bantamweight in that time), he moved to Belarus in 1999.

Khatsigov won a gold medal at the [[2002 European Amateur Boxing Championships]] in [[Perm, Russia]].

He qualified for the [[2004 Summer Olympics]] by ending up in second place at the [[4th AIBA European 2004 Olympic Qualifying Tournament]] in [[Baku, Azerbaijan]]. In Athens, Greece he defeated [[Juan Manuel López (boxer)]] but lost in the second round of the [[Boxing at the 2004 Summer Olympics – Bantamweight|Bantamweight (54 kg)]] division to Thailand's eventual runner-up [[Worapoj Petchkoom]].

He also qualified for the [[2008 Summer Olympics]], but was edged out by [[Veaceslav Gojan]] in his first bout.

